  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n`@QuarkusIntegrationTest` classes that launch a container for each `@Test` use `DefaultDockerContainerLauncher.start` to send container output to `Path logFile = PropertyTestUtil.getLogFilePath()`, which is helpful... but it gets truncated at the start of every test by `Files.deleteIfExists(logFile)`.\r\n\r\nSuspending tests interactively can facilitate manual log inspection, but ultimately that log output should _all_ be retained at the end of mvn verify to support CI/CD pipelines where developers will need to consult container output to diagnose integration test failures.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nA system property that allows `DefaultDockerContainerLauncher.start` to skip log file truncation would do the trick, I think.  For my use case, an option to set `ProcessBuilder().inheritIO()` would also be handy.",
